knowledge_graph.title: Ravioli
knowledge_graph.description: Ravioli are a type of stuffed pasta comprising a filling enveloped in thin pasta dough. Usually served in broth or with a sauce, they originated as a traditional food in Italian cuisine. Ravioli are commonly square, though other forms are also used, including circular and semi-circular.

related_questions.question: What is traditionally in ravioli?
related_questions.snippet: Common fillings of ravioli include ricotta, spinach, nutmeg, black pepper, and lemon rind. Internationally, March 20 is Ravioli Day. Still a popular pasta today, ravioli's roots can be traced way back to at least the 14th century.

related_questions.snippet: Italian ravioli is a delicious dish made with a variety of fillings, including meat, cheese, and vegetables. The most traditional ravioli is made with a filling of ground beef, Parmesan cheese, and eggs.

related_questions.question: Is ravioli a tortellini?
related_questions.snippet: Ravioli are square and tortellini are ring shaped, but both make for hearty meals and are filled with cheese, meat, and more. There are many different types of stuffed pastas, including baked dishes like stuffed shells and manicotti, as well as more recent inventions like stuffed rigatoni.

related_questions.question: Is ravioli plural or singular?
related_questions.snippet: Ravioli [raˈvjɔːli] (plural form; singular: raviolo) are a type of dumpling composed of a filling sealed between two layers of thin pasta dough.
